The Genital Warriors
7.8
AdvertisementBy DANIEL M. GOLDThe worst thing about “Frank Ewington, an elderly patient in a psychiatric ward in Hamburg, Germany, awakens one morning itching to bang out a screenplay, one that has two old lovers of his, Lena and Barbara, meeting on a park bench and learning that, decades earlier, they both had failed relationships with Frank as well as with his nemesis, Viktor. With the help of a magic wand, the women travel back in time, initially to take revenge on the men who done them wrong.From there, events occur as if hurled from a salad spinner. Matthew O. L. Way, the film’s writer and director, is enamored with the concept of The movie just barely avoids being insufferable because of its low-key humor and quick pace. Even so, it’s hard enough for whimsy to sustain a five-minute sketch; expecting it to fuel an existential flight of fancy all but ensures a flameout.




